The government has challenged institutions of higher learning and especially public universities to innovate ways of alternative funding to enhance financial sustainability*****principal secretary for university education, Simon Nabukwesi says many public universities are struggling with funding inadequacies, which are hampering research and other learning processes, warning that unless the trend changes, the future of the institutions of higher learning looks bleak. The ps spoke at the Jomo Kenyatta university of agriculture and technology&rsquo;s 36th&nbsp;graduation. A total of 4,332 graduands were awarded certificates, diplomas and degrees in various fields during the event that was conducted virtually.
